and honestly if you follow me and you've done this let this just.....be a gentle nudge lol

let's just say it's 100000% okay to just put "hello, can you draw this character in this pose please" instead of "mMMmMmmM he's got his sexy coccus out cause he's so hornie and can't stand it hUf Huff beggin for cream hoe" LIKE. PLEASE I HAVE TO READ THI,S

and when it's nsfw comms i've also had ppl like...write straight up fic in their comm requests and i can't tell you how awkward it is, i get that it's basically porn but i'm doing this very much as a job and having to see ppl essentially get themselves off in google forms is...

also the more visual you can be the better. even if u have to draw a stick figure or find stock photos. it saves my life thank you

this isn't to say you can't mention backstories or personalities at all, just. understand it might make the process actually harder if too long

all artists work differently and some probably value extra info like backstories, but in my case if it's not relevant it muddles the image and takes away from the descriptive parts that i need to work with

it's interesting to see other ppl talk about it because i just assumed it was my own shortcomings, that i can't absorb text as well as i'd like etc. but it's happened so many times that i've missed things no matter how many times i go over a description

yeah....i hesitate to mention stuff like this sometimes but at least in my case i am...literally begging you for your own sake to keep descriptions brief and relevant. because i will have to reread it lots. and i WILL miss things the longer it is, i can't help it. https://t.co/BoP6gqu3MF
